    <bioghist>Merrill (Fred) Kershner, of Boyne City, Mich., served in the 576th Ambulance Company, U.S. Army, during World War II. He was taken prisoner by Germans in Sept. 1944 and was confined for 8 months in Stalag 7A, Moosburg, Germany.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>Logbook containing sketches (many by fellow prisoner John Endsley), autographs, poetry, plays attended, snapshots, and memorabilia; also photographs and miscellaneous items.</scopecontent>
